      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "NERANO NZ (4) has the hoof on the till having come from wider barriers for second in both starts since returning to Sydney and Jason Grimson. Should be close to his peak now and a more favourable draw could see him break through. PINSEEKER NZ (10) had to race wide without cover in his Miracle Mile qualifier last start so was far from disgraced when only 6.7m from the winner. Has transferred to Luke McCarthy since and came from this barrier when winning at this circuit and distance two back. Strong claims. KINGMAKER NZ (9) hasn't missed the top-three in five starts this time in, winning at this circuit and distance two back. Drew wide and worked but stuck on for a 4m second last time. Must respect. BETTERTHANCASH NZ (3) draws well and is close to peaking now having put the writing on the wall when placed from a wider barrier last time. Tough draw for STENO (11) but she is a good mare who is up to this with some luck.",
